In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, @Tunisian Spice Blend{1/4%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining Tunisian Spice later.) Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary; place in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} (use a #large microwave-safe bowl{} for 4 servings) with a splash of @water{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}, then drain.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, as much @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} as you like, and a pinch of @Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon} to taste (add more if you like a smokier flavor). Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining Tunisian Spice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is taking longer to cook through, cover pan for the last few minutes of cooking.

In the last minute of cooking, reduce heat to medium and add @Butter{1%tablespoon} to pan. Once melted, spoon over chicken to coat.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

While chicken rests, remove green beans from bowl; pat dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add green beans; cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until green beans are browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Sliced Almonds{1/2%ounce}, @Golden Raisins{1%ounce}, and @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide rice, green beans, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with as much creamy paprika sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining sauce on the side.